<html><head><meta content="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1" http-equiv="content-type"><title>Adding or Changing Course Information for Credentialing</title></head><body style="color: rgb(0, 0, 102); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 204);" alink="#000099" link="#000099" vlink="#990099">
<h1><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">Adding or Changing Coursework Information for Credentialing </span></h1>
<br style="font-family: Century Gothic;">
<span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">This resource summarizes
guidelines and information for documenting faculty coursework for
credentialing purposes. required for listing coursework information. </span><br style="font-family: Century Gothic;">
<br style="font-family: Century Gothic;">
<span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">The following information
must be included on the roster when documenting 18 graduate semester
hours of coursework in the teaching: </span><br style="font-family: Century Gothic;">
<ul>
  <li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">Course number </span></li>
  <li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">Course title </span></li>
  <li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">Name of institution where course was taken</span></li>
  <li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">Course credit hours (the wizard will automatically adjust credit hours earned on a quarterly semester basis)</span></li>
</ul>
<br>
<table style="text-align: left; width: 1306px; background-color: rgb(153, 0, 0); color: white; height: 176px;" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="vertical-align: top;"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">Please Note: Credit hours in the following types of courses cannot be counted to satisfy the 18-hour requirement: </span><br style="font-family: Century Gothic;">

      <ul>
<li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">internship</span></li><li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">practicum</span></li><li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">dissertation or thesis </span></li><li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">independent study</span></li><li><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;">topics courses, unless topic relates to instructional area</span></li>
      </ul>

      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<br style="font-family: Century Gothic;">
<span style="font-family: Century Gothic;"></span><br style="font-family: Century Gothic;">
</body></html>